race.comment: FRANKELY SUBLIME (2) heads a strong Waller team. Returned over 1250m last start and found the line well to get up for second at this track. Not drawn the best but with even luck she is a great chance to break through. $3 million yearling ERNAUX (3) resumed in the same race as Frankley Sublime a fortnight ago and was disappointing as favourite, tiring to miss the placings. Best run last prep was second-up when a close third at Canterbury. Can improve enough to give this a shake. ROSA INCANTA (1) raced back in the field and wide before closing well to finish fifth when resuming in a strong form race over 1200m at Rosehill a month ago. Kept fresh and will find this easier so she is right in contention. MILLY MOLLY MANDY (14) has raced twice this prep and been safely held in country maidens. Worth one more chance with the blinkers back on. PURPLE ROSE (13) is back for a second campaign. Placed three from five when last in work and her trial form is outstanding.
